The template string format for elseif hydration markers appears incorrect. Based on the client-side parsing logic in if.js line 67, the format expects content like `[1]` inside the comment. The current format `<!--[${index++}-->` produces `<!--[1-->` which would cause `parseInt(data.substring(1))` to return NaN because `parseInt("[1-->")` = NaN. The correct format should include the closing bracket before the HTML comment end: `<!--[${index++}]-->` which produces `<!--[1]-->`, allowing `parseInt("[1]-->")` = 1 to work correctly.

```suggestion
		alternate.body.unshift(
